description:
“THE SON OF SUPERMAN” Chapter One

The Last Son of Krypton must decide whether to help his young son use his new and rapidly increasing abilities, or hide them from the world.

THE CREATORS: The team supreme that brought fans the adventures of Damian Wayne in BATMAN AND ROBIN returns for the adventures of Superman and his offspring.

NOW SHIPPING TWICE MONTHLY!

This story takes place after Superman: Rebirth #1. At Hamilton County, Lois and Clark are trying to build a new life with their son, Jonathan Kent. However, it seems that hiding their secret identity isn't easy, especially for Jon.

Synopsis

Clark Kent is mourning the death of Superman (New52 incarnation) at his grave alongside Pa and Ma Kent's graves. He realizes that this world still needs a Superman, therefore he dons the cape once more.

In the evening, Clark wakes up due to the lightning. Unfortunately, it hit their barn, leaving the animals in danger. Clark goes in the barn and saves the animals before they get hurt.

The next day, Jon asks him if they are going to build the barn. Clark tells him that they have other chores to do first. Clark wants Jon to promise him he won't use his powers. Jon promises his dad and leaves with his cat Goldie to fill the corn harvester.

As Jon is running behind Goldie, a hawk is approaching Goldie and manages to grab him, at a fast pace. Jon is furious and wants his cat back, using his heat vision at the hawk would be the solution. Conversely, both the hawk and Goldie are dead. Saddened by the fact that his cat is now dead, he's also broken his promise. Moreover, his neighbour, Kathy Branden, has seen him using his powers.

At dinner, Lois and Clark are having a conversation whereas Jon barely talks. After Kathy stops by their house to offer them milk, Lois and Clark both agree it will be nice to have a neighbour at Jon's age. Jon disagrees and finds nothing nice about it. Everything they do is a secret, his dad's secretly a superhero and his mom writes books under a secret name. In addition, Jon is secretly half human and half kryptonian. Clark tells him to go to his room to blow off steam.

In his bedroom, he sneakily watches his dad discussing something with Batman and Wonder Woman. The Trinity turn their head and look at Jon, all of a sudden. Jon is surprised and immediately disappears in front of the window. His dad enters his room and tells him to come with him.

description:
“THE SON OF SUPERMAN” Chapter Two: In #2, Superboy takes flight as he accompanies his father, the Man of Steel, on their first mission together to confront a creature more dangerous than anyone realizes. Will the duo triumph...or will they die when they face the lethal force of the Eradicator?

In this story, Superman teaches his son how to use his powers. Later, Jon and Kathy have a talk. A new threat is coming.

Synopsis

Clark takes his son to his first "mission", saving a sub from a huge one-eyed tentacle monster. Clark tells Jon to watch, listen and learn. Unfortunately, the monster attacks Jon, Clark acts fast and opens its eye. Clark tells Jon to use his heat vision precisely, but he was too reckless. Second time, Clark tells him that he can do it, he's his son. Jon focuses and blasts one more time, this time effectively. The monster leaves, therefore Clark and Jon can return home.

Back at the farm, Jon and Kathy are sitting in a tree, discussing Jon's powers he has yet to control. Kathy reassures him that he will do fine, in fact, she feels safe being around him. The branch breaks in half, Jon falls to the ground. Cobb Branden, Kathy's grandfather brings Jon home, who's a bit injured.

Towards the end of the story, we see a familiar face reaching the Fortress of Solitude, it's none other than the Eradicator.

description:
“THE SON OF SUPERMAN” Chapter Three: In #3, with a touch that means death, the Eradicator proves he’s a match for Superman, but his super-powered offspring may be more than anyone can handle—including the Man of Tomorrow.

The Eradicator has arrived and he's after the Kent family. Can Superman put a stop to it?
Synopsis

Clark and Lois bring their son to the Fortress of Solitude, because their they have access to Kryptonian tech, which they need in order to find out why Jon is still unconscious (after the fall he took back at the barn).

Having entered the Fortress, the first person they stumble upon is the Eradicator. Clark, surprised yet furious, attacks him while asking him how he broke into the Fortress. Lois tells Clark to stop, the walls are already cracking. The fight between the two continues and the walls start collapsing. Lois and Jon are in danger and as the wall collapses, it is the Eradicator who saves them in time. Clark is quite surprised by this and the Eradicator tells him to settle this somewhere else.

Eradicator tells Superman that the Kryptonian race is the one true race. His goal is to preserve the purity of the race. Since Jon is half human and half Kryptonian, he would need to eradicate the "impure" half. After this conversation, Eradicator heads over to Jon and as he opens his mouth to eradicate him, Krypto jumps at the right moment in front of Jon, thereby sacrificing himself. Superman doesn't hold his punches, as he beats him continuously without taking a break. Jon is mourning Krypto's death for a wee bit, stands up consumed by rage.

description:
“SON OF SUPERMAN” part four! The battle for Jon hits Metropolis as the Eradicator targets Superman’s son! Can the Man of Steel protect the city and his son against the Kryptonian executioner—or will he have to make a sacrifice?

Superman and Superboy vs the Eradicator. The souls of Krypton are inside the Eradicator.

Synopsis

Superman and his son (Superboy) attack the Eradicator with their combined powers. They bash his head and it looks like they have won, but then the unexpected happens. The souls of Krypton are released. All this time, the souls were inside the Eradicator, but now they're free. Unfortunately, it's not for the good as they claim the bodies of random citizens of Metropolis.

The souls have entered Clark's body as well, or at least under the influence, as he's screaming that they're exiles and that they are lost. However, Pa Kent appears in his subconscious as he tells that it's the duty of the living to carry on the legacy so that the dead can be free.

Clark is now fully in charge of his body. He immediately grabs Lois and Jon, puts them in a sub and flies far, far away.

description:
“SON OF SUPERMAN” part five! The Eradicator is unstoppable and it has forced Superman to leave Earth behind to keep his son from harm.

Superman takes the battle to another place in order to keep Metropolis save. The moon is the perfect place. There's also a convenient place on the moon, the Batcave.

Synopsis

Superman carries Lois and Jon to the moon. Once they are on the moon, they enter the Batcave.

Jon asks his dad to call in the Justice League, they can help them out and have an awesome team-up. Clark refuses, the Justice League is too busy at the moment. Apart from that, they shouldn't know Jon has powers.

The Eradicator interrupts them while they're having a conversation. Superman fights him, but this time the Eradicator acts quickly. He opens his mouth to "eradicate" Superman. Jon tells him to open his mouth or he'll open it for him. Unfortunately, his heat vision has no impact at all.

Jon runs away from the Eradicator, meanwhile Lois puts on the Hellbat suit. Now Jon and Lois strike together.

Superman asks to souls within the Eradicator to help him out one more time. Clark consumes their powers and manages to exit the Eradicator through his mouth. Superman thanks his son and wife for holding their own, he'll take it over from them.

description:
“SON OF SUPERMAN” part 6! The evil Eradicator faces off against Superman and son in a battle that may save the day but destroy the moon.

Superman vs Eradicator, the final battle of this arc where Superman doesn't hold back.

Synopsis

Superman attacks the Eradicator, but this time it's different. This time, Superman goes all-out against Eradicator.

The Eradicator insists that Jon is a mistake due to him being a half-breed. Clark finds this absurd and tells him that he's completely wrong.

Superman reaches for Krypto (who's still inside Eradicator) and tells him to follow Superman's voice and bite his way out. That is exactly what Krypto does, as he rips Eradicator chest in half.

Citizens of Metropolis are watching footage of the Moon where Superman has defeated the Eradicator. Not only Metropolis, but the whole world is seeing this. The citizens are baffled, in a positive way, as they now trust this incarnation of Superman and want him to remain on planet Earth.

There's one welcoming surprise for Jon: Superman introduces him to Batman and Wonder Woman as the new Superboy!

description:
“SON OF SUPERMAN” part 7! In this epilogue issue, Superman considers the toll his battles with the Eradicator and Doomsday have taken on his family and the need for a normal life. But can the Man of Steel ever take a day off?

Clark decides to spend his day with his family. It's the final night of the Hamilton County Fair, the perfect oppurtunity!

Clark wants to have a nice family get-together for a change. Lois agrees provided that he won't don the cape or as she calls it "superman-ing". Clark assures her, he won't do that and gives her his cape to prove it.

It's evening and the Kent family arrive at the County Fair. There are all sorts of entertainment for everyone. Jon is having the time of his life.

There are some men rather secretive at the Fair. There are always people who ruin things and as it turns out, those men are planning something heinous. It's not clear what they have up their sleeve, but they do have guns at their disposal.

Clark notices it due to his super hearing but there's nothing he can do due to the his promise to Lois. However, some time later he did manage to hand them over to the police by wearing medieval clothes.

Ultimately, they ride on a rollercoaster while they hear the men talking about a weird guy handing over criminals to the police. Lois is infuriated, but Clark and Jon ignore it and yell "up, up and away!".

description:
“RETURN TO DINOSAUR ISLAND” part one! Father and Superson work on a science assignment with bizarre consequences that transports the pair along with Krypto to Dinosaur Island! Now, amid relics of World War II, Superman tries to keep Jon from the jaws of prehistoric predators! Worse, Kal-El can’t find a way to fly off the Island.

Superboy is working on his school assignment when he, his dad and Krypto are suddenly transported to Dinosaur Island.

Jon is working on his school assignment. Jon tells his dad that the object is not a drone but a “flying saucer”. It flies away, Krypto reacts on command and bites on the object. Jon tells him to stop before it breaks. Then, unexpectedly, the three of them are transported to Dinosaur Island.

Clark realises that the device may be their only way back home. Therefore, they want to find it immediately. This may not be as simple as they thought, since there are dinosaurs on the lookout, hunting for their flesh.

One predatory dinosaur manages to eat Krypto. Fortunately, Jon rescues his dog from the dinosaur before it’s too late.

description:
“RETURN TO DINOSAUR ISLAND” part two! Trapped on a strange island removed from time, Superman and Son encounter a lone survivor from the past. He may hold the key to their escape, but first they must survive the other denizens of the Island.

Superman, Supberboy and Krypto are still stuck on Dinosaur Island. Thanks to some help by a new friend, they escape, but not without a cost.

Superman, Superboy and Krypto are in a cave reading a lengthy text on a wall. It appears that it’s written by the group The Losers. Shortly after reading the text, a man shoots at them. This man is Captain Storm. He thought that they were intruders, since the entire Island has been trying to kill him ever since he landed on it.

Now that they now they are all on the same side, they want to find a way to leave the Island as soon as possible.

They find the transporter cube, but it’s in possession of an army of Dinosaurs who aren’t willing to give it back to them. At last, after a massive clash, Jon manages to grab it.

Clark tells Storm to join them, he could finally leave this disastrous place. However, he refuses and tells them that he’s already home. This leaves the trio no choice but to leave.

description:
“IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER” part one! For the first time, the Man of Tomorrow and the Boy of Steel team up with the Caped Crusader and the Boy Wonder in a father-son adventure you won’t want to miss! Damian Wayne has been hearing a lot about this mysterious new Superboy, and now’s his chance to find out who he is...

Jon and Damian’s first encounter where they don’t get on with each other at all. Damian doesn’t trust him and with the help of Maya, he kidnaps Jon.

Jon and Kathy are walking on the schoolyard. Jon notices a girl who suddenly drops all her books. Jon helps her and this girls turns out to be Maya Ducard, a.k.a Nobody. Nobody, who has befriended Damian, is secretly spying Jon and shares the information with Damian.

In the afternoon, Jon is heading home. Then he’s attacked by Nobody and Goliath. Jon sneezes, causing a freeze breath. However, this is not his intention. Jon falls to the ground but fortunately Goliath softens the fall.

When Jon wakes up he finds himself in the Batcave. Damian wants to interrogate him, but Batman tells him to stop. Superman breaks in and blames Batman. Jon sneezes once again, causing an “ice wall” between Superman and Batman. Superman realises that his son needs his help and discusses the situation with Batman.

description:
“IN THE NAME OF THE FATHER” part two! Superman and Batman are up against the ropes, and it’s up to Superboy and Robin to save the day— but can they work together long enough to get the job done?

After their clash in the previous issue, Damian and Jon now have to work together at the bootcamp.

Batman and Superman decide there is only one way their sons will work (hopefully bond as well) together: bootcamp.

At the bootcamp, Jon and Damian come across Maya, who makes it hard for duo. The duo manages to beat her, but then the next opponent appears: Goliath. Initially, Goliath blocks their way but subsequently he decides to help them.

After a long and tiresome day, but a successful day regardless, the boys take some rest. The next day, Batman, Superman and Alfred compliment the boys for their hard work. Alfred calls them the Super Sons.

description:
“SINISTER PURPOSE” part one! Frankenstein has come to Hamilton County, home of Superman, and Hell has come with him. It’s Man of Steel vs. the Monster to save the life of someone in the town with a horrifying secret.

Lois has an appointment at the Hamilton Horn. She is welcomed by a woman called Candice. This woman, however, turns out to be an alien.

Lois Lane, formerly known as the famous Daily Planet reporter has now an appointment at the Hamilton Horn.

She is told that her articles are impeccable. Candice wants it to keep it short and tells her that she’s a good fit.

While she is rambling on, Frankenstein wrecks the place and starts hurting Candice. Lois tells him to leave her alone, but he doesn’t listen. Lois puts on her Hell-Bat glove and fends him off for a while before they leave.

Superman arrives and has an epic battle with Frankenstein. Ultimately, Frankenstein holds Candice up and cuts her face. Candice is not a human, in fact, she’s an alien who's called Kroog.

description:
“SINISTER PURPOSE” part two ! Here comes the Bride and her four arms are loaded with weapons. And on what side of those guns is Lois Lane going to be? The mystery of one of the citizens of Hamilton will be exposed with monstrous consequences for all.

Kroog has been on the run for a while, but Frankenstein has finally found him. Lady Frankenstein would like to bring Kroog to justice.

Frankenstein has proved Lois and Clark wrong, since it’s not Candice but an alien impersonating as Candice. Superman is glad that he’s brought to justice, but he’s disgruntled at the fact the he knew nothing about the S.H.A.D.E operation beforehand.

Frankenstein tells him that he’s had no choice, since this would be a “smash and grab” mission. Superman tells his that this could have cost lives, this required judicious thought and planning.

Lady Frankenstein, whom Frankenstein refers to as his bride, interrupts the conversation and approaches Kroog. Unexpectedly, Kroog pulls a trick and disappears. With the assistance of Superman, they find Kroog once again, but this time lock him up.

Frankenstein wants to rekindle with his ex, but to no avail. She leaves and doesn’t accept his ring.

description:
“MULTIPLICITY” part one! The New Super-Man of China has been taken! The Red Son Superman of Earth-30 has been beaten! And who knows what’s happened to Sunshine Superman! Someone is collecting Supermen across the Multiverse—this looks like a job for our Kal-El as he is joined by Justice Incarnate in this multi-Earth epic!

Clark Kent is driving his car when suddenly Superman appears in front of the car. This version of Superman has come to warn main Earth Superman of the upcoming threat, the Gatherers.

Clark Kent a.k.a. Superman is driving his car in civilian clothes. He abruptly stops the car due to the fact that someone stands in front of the car, it’s none other than Superman from Earth-30 a.k.a. Red Son Superman. He looks exhausted, tells him that threats are coming their way. Clark responds and Russian Superman is surprised since he’d thought that Clark’s Russian would have been rusty, yet it is near perfect.

They try to leave as soon as possible, but to no avail, the Gatherers encroach upon their territory. They have some trouble initially but the duo manage to beat all of them. The Justice Incarnate arrive just after the battle. Calvin Ellis a.k.a Superman of Earth-23 tells Superman that these creatures are after all Supermen of the Multiverse.

Kenan Kong, the Superman of China is training, but the Gatherers attack him from behind and manage to capture him. There’s a place where they lock up all Superman they’ve caught so far, one of them is Captain Carrot.

description:
“MULTIPLICITY” part two! Superman and New Super-Man fight alongside an army of Supermen from across the Multiverse against the threat trying to wipe them all out of existence! Plus, Jon and his neighbor Kathy investigate a hidden horror that seems to be growing in their town.

Superman and the Justice Incarnate want to warn other Supermen, in order to do that they travel through the Multiverse and gather all the Supermen. Some are willing to listen, whilst others are stubborn and put up a fight. They eventually succeed and return to their special ship called the Ultima Thule. Superman makes sure all other Superman are safe and teleports them away while he remains on the ship, waiting for Prophecy.

description:
“MULTIPLICITY” finale! Superman, New Super-Man and Justice Incarnate make their last stand against their multiverse-spanning foe, and the Man of Steel discovers another clue to the truth of his existence.

Prophecy has captured Superman and throws him into a pit. Here, he meets other Supermen who were already captured. Subsequently, a familiar face joins them, it's Kenan, the Superman of China. Superman introduces himself to Kenan and they both agree they'd expected their first meeting to be different.

Ultimately, the Supermen are able to beat Prophecy. It seems that Prophecy dies, however that's not the case at all. He's vanished and now he's locked up by Mr. Oz himself.

description:
“DARK HARVEST”! Jon and Cathy go deep into the woods of Hamilton to find a horror that hungers for the new Superboy!

Kathy asks Jon for his help. Their cow, Bessie, has been missing for a while now and she needs his help. Jon is willing to help and together they seek their cow in Dead Man's Swamp. It's gotten the horror vibe especially since it's dark outside and there's a creepy figure observing them from the distance. They eventually find Bessie and decide it's for the best to go home.

description:
“SUPERMAN REBORN” part one! In DC UNIVERSE: REBIRTH #1, the enigmatic Mr. Oz told this Superman, “You and your family are not what you believe you are. And neither was the fallen Superman.” Now, in the first Rebirth crossover between SUPERMAN and ACTION COMICS, the shocking truth behind Oz’s words is revealed. It begins with one of Oz’s prisoners escaping, and ends in a tragic moment for Lois and Superman.

The covers by Patrick Gleason and Mick Gray and the variant covers by Gary Frank for SUPERMAN #18-19 and ACTION COMICS #975-976 will connect to form a single vertical image.

In the beginning of the issue we see Mr. Oz's prisoners. Then there's one empty room with drawings of Superman on the walls. We don't know to who or what it alludes to but it would make sense if it's the imposter Clark Kent. This imposter Clark Kent is the one who has kidnapped Jon Kent.

description:
“SUPERMAN REBORN” part three! In the penultimate chapter of this tale the life of Superman’s son hangs in the balance—and the Man of Steel faces the truth about his life!

The covers by Patrick Gleason and Mick Gray and the variant covers by Gary Frank for SUPERMAN #18-19 and ACTION COMICS #975-976 will connect to form a single vertical image.

It turns out the imposter Clark Kent is in fact Mister Mxyzptlk! He's mad at Superman due to him not rescuing him from Oz's cells. Superman says that he didn't know, but alas, it's too late now and as a punishment he makes Lois & Clark forget that they have a son.
This all happens while Clark was playing Mxy's "game", which was to find Jon in time. Jon yells that he is his son and then Clark suddenly remembers and finds his son.

description:
“BREAKING POINT” Part 1

Lois Lane is after the interview of a lifetime. The subject of her Daily Planet article… Deathstroke the Terminator. Determined to get “inside the mind of a killer”, Lois follows a trail of bodies across the globe and comes face to face with the ultimate assassin. But the encounter turns deadly and, with Superman half a world away, the interview of a lifetime could cost Lois Lane her life!

description:
“IMPERIUS LEX!” It’s a game of thrones on Apokolips as the lords of the dreaded world battle each other to claim its rule. Lex Luthor is summoned back to the warring planet, and he will need Superman to help him reclaim a crown he did not ask for. Meanwhile, Lois is confronted by the Female Furies and Jon faces the Children of the Firepits.

description:
“SUPER SONS OF TOMORROW” part one! The four-part crossover between Superman, the Super Sons and the Teen Titans starts here! The Batman of Tomorrow travels to the present to prevent a cataclysmic disaster before it happens, revealing that Superboy will soon be responsible for the death of millions. But Superman will do anything to protect his son…and the Batman of Tomorrow is unwavering in his resolve to take down the Boy of Steel. Don’t miss a clash of titanic proportion in the opening chapter of this game-changing story!

description:
“BOYzarro RE-DEATH” part two! What do you get when you try to fit a boy from a square planet into a round one? Boyzarro! Superboy and Kathy try to keep the lid on their Bizarro-sized can of worms as Boyzarro tears a rage-filled path of destruction from Metropolis to Hamilton and beyond! But what happens when Superman and Bizarro find out what their kids have been up to?
